"O - Just not hitting on all cylinders. I wouldn't reach for this often when compared to other milk stouts."
""
"i am surprised people are so down on this one. usually it is me who knocks the over hyped prairie stuff, not the other way around. i like this for being a little different, and while i dont think its their best work, its certainly quality beer. what i like about it is the milk stout part, its different in that while you can taste the lactose, it isnt all that sweet, in fact, its quite dry. uncommon for the style to have the flavor there, but have it dry out like that in the finish. i credit a dusty cocoa type malt, unsweetened bakers chocolate notes, and a very hearty yeast strain for this phenomenon. i am used to crazy yeast in their beer, and although this isnt crazy in the usual funked out barny sense of the term, its crazy because of its completeness, even in a sweet stout style. i like the frothy feel and all the body, and i like that its gone on the swallow. a cool release for spring too, as we are now moving away form stout season, but this one seems to fit, prolonging the seasonality of one of my favorite styles. well done this time around from prairie, thanks for making something a little out of your comfort zone!"
"Personally, I felt that this beer is underrated.  As a sucker for stouts, I picked up a bottle despite the sub-par ratings.  Poured black with small head that disappeared quickly.  I picked up a little malt on the nose, but more of the lactose came through.  Taste is smooth and creamy, with a touch of sweetness.  Just a hint of chocolate.  Very easy drinking."
