"Pours black with a slight khaki head that totally recedes before I get around to taking my first sip. Aroma is decent; sweet and slightly roasty with lactose sugars, milk chocolate, and some caramel. Probably the only good thing about this beer. Flavor tastes like water with milk chocolate mixed in.  Mouthfeel is offensively thin and prickly. If the watered down flavor didn't kill the beer, this horrible mouthfeel certainly would. Overall, I don't know what happened here but this one is no good. My impression is that this is the product of bad brewing, not a bad recipe. It will be a struggle to get through this 4 pack, and 2 of the bottles (if not 3) will likely be drainpours."
