"12 ounce bottle.  Served in a Prairie Teku, the beer pours dark brown/black with a half inch tan head that fizzled away quickly.  Pretty much no lacing at all.  The brew smells like milk and bittersweet chocolate, coffee, and roasted malt.  Taste is similar to the aroma, but there's also some dark fruit and a Nestle Quik/chocolate syrup mixed with milk flavor noticeable too.  Just too much of an artificial chocolate flavor.  I liked this when I first started drinking it, but unfortunately it only got worse after the first sip.  Mouthfeel/body is light/medium, seems a bit watery and thin to me.  This isn't a bad brew at all, but I expect better out of Prairie.  However, at $2.99 a bottle I guess I shouldn't complain too much.  Worth a try once, but I won't be trying this again anytime soon."
